{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MMbtCYcqgfnLrqVSqKrXBw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Symphonia already has `\"isomp4\", \"aac\"` features enabled for AAC, and I need to add `\"flac\"` for FLAC decoding. For encoding: FLAC output can be saved as WAV (lossless→lossless is fine), and AAC input gets decoded then saved as WAV or MP3. There's no pure-Rust AAC or FLAC encoder readily available, so the approach is:\n\n1. Add `\"flac\"` to symphonia features\n2. Add `Flac` and `Aac` variants to `AudioFormat`\n3. Use the symphonia-based decoder (generalized) for FLAC and AAC loading\n4. For saving: FLAC/AAC inputs save as WAV by default (since we don't have encoders for those)\n\nLet me also check what CLI help text references formats."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1027,"cache_read_input_tokens":62174,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1027},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9bd7957-c8f2-4e48-8fcc-7059d242854c","uuid":"4dca039b-713c-45aa-8acc-3efabe459d9a"}
